understanding of the city, one that goes beyond the headlines. The result is a passionate, well-written portrait of a legendary and ever-evolving place.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aCity and town lifezNew York (State)zNew YorkvAnecdotes. 7aLITERARY COLLECTIONS / American / General.2bisacsh1 aAciman, André, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBahrampour, Tara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarry, Dan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeller, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBotti, David C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCharyn, Jerome, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCunningham, Laura Shaine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDwyer, Jim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEisenstadt, Jill, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGornick, Vivian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGussow, Mel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHanson, Ivor, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaskell, Molly, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHustvedt, Siri, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJamieson, Wendell, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKim, Suki, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKlosterman, Chuck, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKurutz, Steven, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeBlanc, Adrian Nicole, econtri